  "description": "<p>\n\t<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://i1.s.hjfile.cn/fanli/201303/24da5bbe-bf4d-45c6-b822-6a24d787ac41.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 273px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p720204\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\tThis is Science in Action from the BBC. I'm Jon Stewart. Coming up, there can be few things more annoying than someone talking loudly on their mobile phone. But why is it so much more <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/irritating\" target=\"_blank\">irritating</a>, and so much harder to ignore than just overhearing a full conversation? New research may have the answer, later in the programme. First though, to Mars, NASA's Curiosity rover has been phoning home with the results of new experiments this week, which suggest that <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/condition\" target=\"_blank\">conditions</a> on the Red Planet may have supported life. Mars is, of course now, dry and <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/dusty\" target=\"_blank\">dusty</a>, but it seems that wasn't always the case. Our space <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/expert\" target=\"_blank\">expert</a>, BBC Science Correspondent Jonathan Amos is here. Jon, what exactly have they found?</p>\n<p>\n\tWell, this is actually a very interesting development, because we've been looking down at Mars now for many years at the types of minerals that are on the surface. And there's a particular type that we're really after those clay minerals, and the reason for that is because clays are indicative of a process whereby water, starts to break down rock. It's at a process that goes on for a long time. And critically, it's neutral water. If you look at many of the rocks that we've seen on Mars today with the other rovers, Spirit, Opportunity, the environments in which those rocks were lay down were quite <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/acidic\" target=\"_blank\">acidic</a>. Very briny, not very nice places, if you were a <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/microbe\" target=\"_blank\">microbe</a>. What this latest discovery from Curiosity tells us is that there was billions of years ago on the surface of Mars, an environment that actually was very benign, very favourable for life, probably a lakebed, something like that, where the water was pretty much fresh water. You could have picked it up in a cup if you were there and drunk it.</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 128, 128); line-height: 25px; font-family: verdana, arial;\">声明：音视频均来自互联网链接，仅供学习使用。本网站自身不存储、控制、修改被链接的内容。&ldquo;沪江</span><a class=\"creatLinks\" href=\"http://st.hujiang.com/tag/%E8%8B%B1%E8%AF%AD/\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 90, 148); line-height: 25px; font-family: verdana, arial; text-decoration: none; border-bottom-color: rgb(0, 90, 148); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dashed;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"更多英语内容\">英语</a><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 128, 128); line-height: 25px; font-family: verdana, arial;\">&rdquo;高度重视知识产权保护。当如发现本网站发布的信息包含有侵犯其著作权的链接内容时，请联系我们，我们将依法采取措施移除相关内容或屏蔽相关链接。</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p720204/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p720204\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p710386/\">比尔盖茨推荐2014年5本必读好书</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p720267/\">50岁老人希望自己在25岁做的事</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p431046/\">告别单身从朋友下手 7招将朋友变成恋人</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http